article.description: Bo Hodges had 26 points plus 12 rebounds as East Tennessee State romped past VMI 94-70 on Thursday night. Daivien Williamson added 20 points for the Buccaneers.
article.headline: Hodges leads E. Tennessee St. over VMI 94-70
article.linkText: Hodges leads E. Tennessee St. over VMI 94-70
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. -- Bo Hodges had 26 points plus 12 rebounds as East Tennessee State romped past VMI 94-70 on Thursday night. Daivien Williamson added 20 points for the Buccaneers. Hodges hit 10 of 13 shots. Tray Boyd III had 18 points for East Tennessee State (22-7, 12-4 Southern Conference). Jeromy Rodriguez added seven rebounds. Patrick Good scored only 2 points. The Buccaneers' leading scorer coming into the contest at 12 points per game, he failed to make a shot from beyond the arc (0 of 5). Myles Lewis scored a career-high 27 points for the Keydets (7-20, 1-14), who have now lost eight games in a row. Sarju Patel added 12 points. Bubba Parham, the Keydets' leading scorer heading into the matchup at 21 points per game, was held to 2 points on 0-of-12 shooting. The Buccaneers improve to 2-0 against the Keydets for the season. East Tennessee State defeated VMI 85-82 on Jan. 17. East Tennessee State plays UNC Greensboro on the road on Sunday. VMI takes on Western Carolina on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap , using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
